    <section id="introduction">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Lamborghini is an iconic Italian brand known for its luxury sports cars.
        Founded in 1963 by Ferruccio Lamborghini, the company has a rich history
        of innovation and performance in the automotive industry.
      </p>
      <img src="countach.jpg" alt="" />
    </section>

    <section id="founding">
      <h2>Founding</h2>
      <p>
        Ferruccio Lamborghini, a successful businessman in the tractor
        manufacturing industry, founded Automobili Lamborghini in Sant'Agata
        Bolognese, Italy. His goal was to create a high-performance sports car
        that could compete with Ferrari.
      </p>
      <img src="founding.jpg" alt="" />
    </section>

    <section id="key-milestones">
      <h2>Key Milestones</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>1964:</strong> The Lamborghini 350 GT, the company's first
          production car, is introduced.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1966:</strong> The Miura is launched, setting new standards
          for sports car performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>1980s:</strong> Lamborghini introduces models like the
          Countach and the Diablo, which become symbols of exotic car design.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2000s:</strong> The brand experiences a resurgence with models
          such as the Murciélago and Gallardo.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <img src="milestones.jpg" alt="" />
    </section>

    <section id="modern-era">
      <h2>Modern Era</h2>
      <p>
        In recent years, Lamborghini has continued to push boundaries with
        models like the Aventador and Huracán, embracing both advanced
        technology and maintaining its reputation for thrilling performance and
        luxury.
      </p>
      <img src="revuelto.jpg" alt="" />
    </section>

    <section id="legacy">
      <h2>Legacy</h2>
      <p>
        Lamborghini remains a symbol of high performance and luxury, influencing
        the automotive industry and inspiring enthusiasts worldwide. Its
        commitment to innovation and design excellence continues to define its
        legacy.
      </p>
      <img src="legacy.jpg" alt="" />
    </section>
